# GitHub / Vercel sync

When you **change any project source file** (not only when the user asks), do this before finishing:

1. `git status` in the project root
2. If there are changes: `git add` the affected files, `git commit` with a short message describing the change, `git push` to `origin` (usually `main`)

This repo is connected to **Vercel**; pushing to GitHub triggers deployment. Do not leave fixes only local unless the user explicitly wants that.

If push fails (auth/network), tell the user clearly what failed.
